    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the initial 20 min, return the <strong>browned chicken</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped green beans</strong>,<strong> spinach</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Pour in the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>red Thai stock</strong> with the juice of half your <strong>lime[s]</strong> and cook for a final 8-10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and all of the stock is absorbed – this is your <strong>red Thai-style chicken breast & green bean risotto</strong></p>",
